/home/pat/progs
/home/pat/bin


Only the first two lines of this file are read.


The first line is the place to install the program directory.
Using !inplace will make it install in place without creating
a new directory.


The second line is the place where it should create a symlink
to the binary in the main install directory.  Note that you
will either need to have this directory in your $PATH or
call the program with the path to this directory.





_______________________________________________________
Examples.


---------------------------------
/home/pat/progs
/home/pat/bin
---------------------------------


---------------------------------
!inplace
/home/pat/bin
---------------------------------

---------------------------------
!inplace
.
---------------------------------


---------------------------------
/home/pat/progs
/home/pat/bin
---------------------------------



---------------------------------
/usr/local/share
/usr/local/bin
---------------------------------






